3
00:00:06,435 --> 00:00:08,680
<i>At this very moment
in the town of Coeur d'Louise,</i>

4
00:00:09,015 --> 00:00:12,515
<i>young Lily Charles was 5 years,
16 hours and 2 minutes old.</i>

5
00:00:12,905 --> 00:00:16,760
<i>Three days earlier, her sister Vivian
was born with a hole in her heart.</i>

6
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:20,320
<i>Cardiologists patched the flaw
and Lily received her orders,</i>

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:23,215
<i>put her vulnerable sibling
before herself.</i>

8
00:00:26,785 --> 00:00:30,293
<i>On her 11th birthday, land-loving Lily
was given a backyard pool</i>

9
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:33,405
<i>and a swimming suit
that matched her sister Vivian's.</i>

10
00:00:33,445 --> 00:00:37,040
<i>Lily would soon realize that constant
exposure to her younger sister</i>

11
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:39,120
<i>made Vivian a devoted mimic.</i>

12
00:00:42,945 --> 00:00:45,202
<i>From matching swimsuits
and backyard poolery,</i>

13
00:00:45,242 --> 00:00:47,445
<i>The </i>Darling Mermaid Darlings
<i>were born.</i>

14
00:00:47,485 --> 00:00:50,763
<i>The renowned synchronized swimming
sisters were loyal beyond separation</i>

15
00:00:50,803 --> 00:00:53,095
<i>until Charles Charles.</i>

16
00:00:53,135 --> 00:00:55,834
<i>Engaged to sister Vivian,
but in love with sister Lily,</i>

17
00:00:55,874 --> 00:00:59,862
<i>Charles Charles not only planted
the seeds of betrayal, he sowed them.</i>

18
00:01:00,675 --> 00:01:03,160
<i>Shamed by the affair
with her sister's fiancé,</i>

19
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:06,135
<i>Lily joined the Sisters
of the </i>Divine Magnatum

20
00:01:06,175 --> 00:01:08,960
<i>where she hid her love child
from Vivian and the world.</i>

21
00:01:09,425 --> 00:01:11,760
<i>No sooner was Lily's lovechild born</i>

22
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,304
<i>than Lily had to give her up
to keep the secret.</i>

23
00:01:14,595 --> 00:01:17,645
<i>Somewhere between losing her daughter
and losing her eye,</i>

24
00:01:17,685 --> 00:01:19,480
<i>Lily lost the will to perform.</i>

25
00:01:19,785 --> 00:01:22,641
<i>Lily's daughter, Charlotte,
was raised by her father</i>

26
00:01:22,681 --> 00:01:25,355
<i>and told her mother died
giving birth.</i>

27
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:29,015
<i>When Charlotte's father died,
her mother came back into her life,</i>

28
00:01:29,055 --> 00:01:30,600
<i>but not as her mother,</i>

29
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:31,885
<i>as her aunt.</i>

30
00:01:31,925 --> 00:01:35,235
<i>Incapacitated by the lie,
she was forced to keep telling,</i>

31
00:01:35,275 --> 00:01:37,203
<i>Lily retreated from the world</i>

32
00:01:37,243 --> 00:01:39,587
<i>and took Vivian
and Charlotte with her.</i>

33
00:01:39,845 --> 00:01:41,545
<i>And then, Charlotte died.</i>

34
00:01:41,665 --> 00:01:45,028
<i>At this very moment, Lily and Vivian
were commemorating a birthday,</i>

35
00:01:45,068 --> 00:01:48,831
<i>specifically a half birthday
for their niece/daughter Charlotte,</i>

36
00:01:48,871 --> 00:01:51,640
<i>who passed away
one and one half birthdays ago.</i>

37
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:53,810
She was such a happy girl.

38
00:01:54,445 --> 00:01:58,105
It's as if when she died, the merriment
in this home died with her.

39
00:01:58,145 --> 00:01:59,145
Good Lord!

40
00:01:59,385 --> 00:02:00,635
Sorry for being dismal.

41
00:02:00,675 --> 00:02:03,640
It would be a relief to be
as strong and stoic as you.

42
00:02:05,645 --> 00:02:07,435
Dear me. The <i>Aquacade</i> is in town!

43
00:02:07,475 --> 00:02:09,599
Remember taking Charlotte there
for her half birthdays?

44
00:02:09,775 --> 00:02:12,560
It's as if an angel
called the <i>Papen County Picayune</i>

45
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,655
and placed an ad on the back page.

46
00:02:14,695 --> 00:02:17,440
You done gawking?
The bird cages need fresh liners.

47
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:19,840
Lily, let's go to the <i>Aquacade</i>.

48
00:02:20,465 --> 00:02:24,315
It could be just the thing to help
the gloom pass. Please. For me.

49
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:27,943
<i>Though Lily was weak with grief,
her compulsion</i>

50
00:02:27,983 --> 00:02:31,633
<i>to put her sister's happiness
before her own drove her to say</i>

51
00:02:31,673 --> 00:02:33,085
Find my opera gloves.

52
00:02:33,125 --> 00:02:35,956
All those children,
tourists and culottes,

53
00:02:36,075 --> 00:02:38,280
the place will be
crawling with germs.

54
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,160
<i>And so Vivian made a wish.</i>

55
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:45,085
I can't believe you remembered
my half birthday.

56
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:48,160
- How could we forget?
- You never shutting up about it.

57
00:02:48,465 --> 00:02:50,000
A little something from me.

58
00:02:50,165 --> 00:02:51,207
The first edition.

59
00:02:52,165 --> 00:02:54,480
And it's signed by the author!
Thank you, Emerson.

60
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,275
Now, where's yours,
boyfriend of half birthday girl?

61
00:02:57,315 --> 00:02:59,400
- Ned thinks he's a terrible gift-giver.
- I am.

62
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:01,640
He's obsessed with finding
the gift that doesn't exist.

63
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,585
- It does.
- Then he psychs himself out

64
00:03:03,625 --> 00:03:05,455
to the point where
he doesn't gift anything,

65
00:03:05,495 --> 00:03:08,360
but he's already given me
the greatest gift of all, my life back.

66
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,490
Still, I'm not giving up
finding the perfect gift.

67
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:13,125
What died?

68
00:03:13,510 --> 00:03:15,080
Half a dozen minks, give or take.

69
00:03:15,265 --> 00:03:17,820
Lily asked me to take them
to the furrier for a fluffing.

70
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:20,760
They're going to the <i>Aquacade</i> tonight
to celebrate Chuck's half birthday.

71
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,920
I'm so touched!

72
00:03:22,225 --> 00:03:24,640
- Aren't you touched, Ned?
- I'm not sure. What's an <i>Aquacade</i>?

73
00:03:24,895 --> 00:03:27,698
It's like this travelling water show
and you have divers and swimmers

74
00:03:27,738 --> 00:03:29,170
and breathtaking daredevils.

75
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:30,920
That was I can't tell
on my half birthday

76
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,074
and we'd always go.

77
00:03:32,114 --> 00:03:33,890
That's it, my perfect gift.

78
00:03:34,185 --> 00:03:36,176
I'm gonna buy six tickets
to the <i>Aquacade</i>.

79
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:37,880
- Call Simone.
- In with the flu.

80
00:03:38,145 --> 00:03:40,002
- Olive, call Randy.
- Out with the gout.

81
00:03:40,042 --> 00:03:43,760
- So, four tickets to the <i>Aquacade</i>.
- Double date! Double date!

82
00:03:49,775 --> 00:03:50,985
Prepare to be amazed.

83
00:03:51,025 --> 00:03:53,404
There has not been this much talent
around a body of water

84
00:03:53,444 --> 00:03:55,438
since Moses played the Red Sea.

85
00:03:55,478 --> 00:03:58,280
But first master of ceremonies
is the son Jimmy Neptune!

86
00:03:58,925 --> 00:04:01,080
And solo sensation Sid Tango!

87
00:04:02,313 --> 00:04:05,425
Shark rider Galveston Gus
and his dorsal finned friend Bubba!

88
00:04:05,465 --> 00:04:06,715
And your aunts.

89
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:19,080
They're the Serena and Venus
of water ballet and no-one's looking?

90
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:22,080
No-one's even pretending not to look
when you're actually looking.

91
00:04:22,181 --> 00:04:24,231
<i>But someone was.</i>

92
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,720
The <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i>.

93
00:04:27,195 --> 00:04:28,051
Look, fans.

94
00:04:28,091 --> 00:04:30,515
No, they are not fans.
They're the <i>Aqua Dolls</i>.

95
00:04:30,555 --> 00:04:31,711
<i>The facts were these.</i>

96
00:04:31,796 --> 00:04:34,789
<i>Blanche and Coral Ramora
aka the </i>Aqua Dolls,

97
00:04:34,829 --> 00:04:38,285
<i>shaped their act into a swimming
celebration of the red, white and blue.</i>

98
00:04:38,325 --> 00:04:41,400
<i>But the </i>Aqua Dolls<i> weren't
the only synchronized sister duo,</i>

99
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:45,520
<i>the </i>Darling Mermaid Darlings<i> were too,
and thus, grew a bitter rivalry.</i>

100
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:48,915
- What has you two chumming the waters?
- I could ask the same, chum.

101
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:51,565
The Charles sisters.
Still out of the loop.

102
00:04:51,605 --> 00:04:52,920
How quaint and refreshing.

103
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:56,120
We're tonight's headliners,
didn't you know?

104
00:04:57,225 --> 00:04:58,225
Yo, dolls.

105
00:04:58,755 --> 00:05:01,075
This is our manager,
Blanche's husband.

106
00:05:01,115 --> 00:05:03,315
Insatiable husband. Shane Trickle.

107
00:05:03,555 --> 00:05:06,505
I found him
when we were performing in Honolulu.

108
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:07,440
Hawaii.

109
00:05:07,675 --> 00:05:09,525
Shake tail. Curtains in 20.

110
00:05:09,765 --> 00:05:11,755
Well, off to do what we do best...

111
00:05:11,795 --> 00:05:13,640
Swim for Christ and country.

112
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,440
You might wanna pick a new flag,
one without horizontal stripes.

113
00:05:18,865 --> 00:05:20,617
You know, it's a shame
cutting this short.

114
00:05:20,657 --> 00:05:24,920
- Why don't we meet in our dressing...
- Lavish dressing room, after the show.

115
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,974
That's if the shuttle bus isn't
in a hurry to get you back to the home.

116
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,825
This was an unanticipated stress.
I would like to go.

117
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,965
You think I wanted
to drive 25 miles to a...

118
00:05:43,145 --> 00:05:46,520
family-friendly venue
with its general admission parking lot?

119
00:05:46,855 --> 00:05:48,935
They don't even serve alcohol here!

120
00:05:48,975 --> 00:05:51,345
Oh, my goodness.
You need to sit down at home?

121
00:05:51,385 --> 00:05:54,085
No, we are gonna stand up.

122
00:05:54,925 --> 00:05:57,105
Come on,
this is Charlotte's celebration.

123
00:05:57,145 --> 00:05:58,795
Her memory comes first.

124
00:05:58,886 --> 00:06:01,286
Get out your ticket.
We're wading in.

125
00:06:10,755 --> 00:06:12,155
They look rattled.

126
00:06:12,555 --> 00:06:14,293
This is the worst
that could've happened.

127
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:17,424
I'm gonna have to sneak closer and see
how they're dealing with everything.

128
00:06:21,755 --> 00:06:25,122
The cotton candy vendor's
a very large man with a doubly large...

129
00:06:25,162 --> 00:06:27,162
display of spun candy
to hide behind.

130
00:06:28,435 --> 00:06:31,307
I have to do something. What can I do
from all the way back up here?

131
00:06:31,765 --> 00:06:35,085
I know! Let's lift their spirits
with an aunt chant or the wave.

132
00:06:35,125 --> 00:06:38,325
It's never been more appropriate.
Emerson, you start.

133
00:06:38,871 --> 00:06:40,921
Or something more to the point.

134
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:43,475
Screw the <i>Aqua Dolls</i>!

135
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,480
I got a smile.

136
00:06:53,485 --> 00:06:55,880
Greetings, ladies and gents!

137
00:06:56,585 --> 00:06:59,960
Welcome to my Night
of a Thousand Bubbles!

138
00:07:02,905 --> 00:07:04,955
Is this a frothy crowd or what?

139
00:07:06,525 --> 00:07:08,375
Bubble the shark thinks so!

140
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,480
More from him later.

141
00:07:10,655 --> 00:07:14,255
Thanks for insisting we stay.
Now the task is staying strong.

142
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,900
But right now, let us rise...

143
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:18,720
for our National Anthem...

144
00:07:19,145 --> 00:07:22,956
as interpreted
by those patriotic paddlers:

145
00:07:23,265 --> 00:07:24,400
the <i>Aqua Dolls</i>.

146
00:07:35,545 --> 00:07:39,000
<i>Oh say can you see...</i>

147
00:07:39,495 --> 00:07:40,920
these ladies swim?

148
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,149
Esther Williams would piss
her cotton panel

149
00:07:48,189 --> 00:07:49,752
at the sight of those rocket splits.

150
00:07:49,792 --> 00:07:50,942
Lily, behave.

151
00:07:50,989 --> 00:07:54,320
Though I will admit
Blanche is looking less than buoyant.

152
00:07:55,905 --> 00:07:58,280
Are you kidding?
She's dead in the water.

153
00:08:13,805 --> 00:08:16,505
I must pen a sympathy note
to Coral Ramora.

154
00:08:16,655 --> 00:08:18,104
Don't sign my name to that

155
00:08:18,144 --> 00:08:20,985
"Sorry a shark ate
your bitch of a sister" letter.

156
00:08:21,025 --> 00:08:24,640
- She wouldn't think twice if it was us.
- But to have a sister die.

157
00:08:25,645 --> 00:08:28,000
I don't know how I'd survive
if I lost you.

158
00:08:29,455 --> 00:08:30,920
Who the hell is that?

159
00:08:32,565 --> 00:08:34,855
Vivian Charles
of the <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i>.

160
00:08:34,895 --> 00:08:36,495
Tails, scales and all.

161
00:08:37,505 --> 00:08:40,920
I overheard your verbal skirmish
with the <i>Aqua Dolls</i> last night.

162
00:08:41,195 --> 00:08:45,013
Hoped to grab you after the show,
but it seemed you were swept away by....

163
00:08:45,239 --> 00:08:46,240
departing crowd.

164
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,783
We small-boned persons
are vulnerable

165
00:08:48,823 --> 00:08:52,000
to exoduses of the mass
and panicked variety.

166
00:08:52,185 --> 00:08:55,479
We all thought the Charles sisters
had gone the way of legend,

167
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:56,720
but gee whizz.

168
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:58,960
- What a time for a comeback.
- Come again?

169
00:09:00,525 --> 00:09:04,375
My father owned the <i>Aquacade</i> before me,
his father before him.

170
00:09:04,795 --> 00:09:08,035
That's how I know Sam Neptune
gave the <i>Darlings</i> their first break.

171
00:09:08,075 --> 00:09:09,025
As a boy,

172
00:09:09,365 --> 00:09:11,429
I watched your set
from the water wings every night

173
00:09:11,469 --> 00:09:14,565
and I never forgot the look
of the audience as they soaked it in.

174
00:09:14,605 --> 00:09:16,491
You two have a gift
unlike any I've seen.

175
00:09:16,531 --> 00:09:19,778
- Your swimming brings people joy.
- Our swimming brings...

176
00:09:20,475 --> 00:09:21,680
brought us joy too.

177
00:09:21,805 --> 00:09:23,760
I'm in desperate need
of a new opening act.

178
00:09:24,005 --> 00:09:26,105
Come back to the pool, <i>Mermaids</i>!

179
00:09:26,445 --> 00:09:29,995
After a 24 hour mourning period
for poor Blanche, of course.

180
00:09:30,455 --> 00:09:32,215
- The water's nice.
- We're retired.

181
00:09:32,255 --> 00:09:34,635
People come out of retirement
all the time.

182
00:09:34,675 --> 00:09:37,160
For how many performances
would you want us?

183
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,240
What has gotten into your gills?

184
00:09:39,575 --> 00:09:43,280
- We had our time.
- And here it is, back again.

185
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,920
Well, are we swimmin', women?

186
00:09:47,855 --> 00:09:49,705
Save it. We're in training.

187
00:09:59,625 --> 00:10:02,200
- Do I smell a fish-wich?
- Yes.

188
00:10:02,331 --> 00:10:04,720
- You mind stowin' it away?
- Yes.

189
00:10:14,615 --> 00:10:15,440
All clear.

190
00:10:19,275 --> 00:10:23,187
Sorry to inconvenience, but the scent
of fried flounder takes me back to...

191
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,440
my recent loss.

192
00:10:25,685 --> 00:10:27,985
You come highly recommended, Mr Cod.

193
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:29,832
- The name's...
- Galveston Gus. I know.

194
00:10:29,872 --> 00:10:32,105
I assume your recent loss
is Bubba the shark?

195
00:10:32,145 --> 00:10:33,640
- You heard?
- I was there.

196
00:10:33,845 --> 00:10:36,000
I hope you ain't part
of the negligence suit against me.

197
00:10:36,235 --> 00:10:38,160
Their lawyers wanna take
everything I have,

198
00:10:38,555 --> 00:10:42,200
and that's why I need you,
to prove I wasn't asleep in the saddle.

199
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:43,567
Not much I can do.

200
00:10:43,715 --> 00:10:47,205
300 people saw your great white
make fish food out of that water hoofer.

201
00:10:47,245 --> 00:10:50,795
I know you can't prove
Bubba didn't eat Miss Ramora, he did,

202
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,480
and what a crap last meal
that must've been.

203
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,828
But you can prove
someone else at the <i>Aquacade</i>

204
00:10:56,868 --> 00:10:59,525
let him out of his pen
and caused this horrible accident.

205
00:10:59,565 --> 00:11:01,167
What's got you floating that theory?

206
00:11:01,207 --> 00:11:04,320
I triple check the gate of his paddock
before every performance.

207
00:11:06,416 --> 00:11:07,960
This here is the only way to open it

208
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,600
and it never leaves my person.

209
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:10,877
No, sir.

210
00:11:10,917 --> 00:11:14,720
Someone else opened his pen
and set me and my boy up.

211
00:11:16,273 --> 00:11:19,825
Bubba was my best friend
ever since he was a guppy of a pup.

212
00:11:20,435 --> 00:11:24,080
And the only happiness I will get from
this mess is knowing his name is clear.

213
00:11:24,485 --> 00:11:25,485
So please,

214
00:11:27,706 --> 00:11:29,422
help a sentimental cow-boo guy.

215
00:11:32,465 --> 00:11:35,365
In third grade,
I did a report on great whites.

216
00:11:35,405 --> 00:11:36,736
It's gonna be a like-a-likes,

217
00:11:36,776 --> 00:11:38,920
seeing as how we're both
misunderstood bad asses.

218
00:11:40,255 --> 00:11:43,937
- Well, this may be a long shot, but...
- Let's give the big fish a fair shake.

219
00:11:54,885 --> 00:11:58,080
Miss Ramora, I'm sorry to inform you,
you've been eaten by Bubba the shark.

220
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:01,125
Did everybody cry?
Of course they did. I'm the fan fav'.

221
00:12:01,165 --> 00:12:03,765
Did you notice
anything strange before...

222
00:12:05,395 --> 00:12:07,400
My sister asked me
if I was going grey.

223
00:12:07,555 --> 00:12:09,480
- How about something pertinent?
- It's strange.

224
00:12:09,695 --> 00:12:11,555
My mother was auburn till the end.

225
00:12:11,595 --> 00:12:14,275
Only other thing that can bring
on grey hair is stress

226
00:12:14,315 --> 00:12:18,175
and my husband Shane
is the biggest stress reliever I know.

227
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:20,200
Big-gest.

228
00:12:20,355 --> 00:12:23,018
I can see something white in there,
but I don't think it's hair.

229
00:12:23,058 --> 00:12:26,195
- It's my hair gel.
- You sure that ain't shark slime?

230
00:12:26,235 --> 00:12:27,998
Water ballerinas use
a very thick hair gel.

231
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:30,837
It's water proof to keep hairstyles
in place. It's kinda like shellac.

232
00:12:30,877 --> 00:12:32,845
Shellac with a faint scent of...

233
00:12:32,885 --> 00:12:33,635
lard.

234
00:12:33,675 --> 00:12:35,815
It's used all the time
in pie crusts.

235
00:12:35,855 --> 00:12:38,595
Why would someone
put pig fat in her hair gel?

236
00:12:38,635 --> 00:12:41,400
Sharks can smell a drop of blood
in the water a quarter of a mile away.

237
00:12:41,615 --> 00:12:43,896
Lard sure as hell
would've prompted Bubba to strike.

238
00:12:43,936 --> 00:12:45,788
All someone would have to do
is open the pen.

239
00:12:45,828 --> 00:12:47,920
We've got bonified murder
by great white.

240
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,750
Wait.

241
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:51,150
Lily and Vivian Charles.

242
00:12:51,532 --> 00:12:55,495
I knew there was a reason they'd come
out of seclusion after all these years.

243
00:12:55,535 --> 00:12:57,800
Shrews. Always after our limelight.

244
00:12:57,880 --> 00:13:00,461
You were the limelight.
You were nothing before the <i>Mermaids</i>.

245
00:13:00,501 --> 00:13:02,600
They put sibling synchro
swim dance on the map.

246
00:13:02,895 --> 00:13:04,680
- Who are you?
- Charlotte Charles.

247
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:07,000
Niece of Vivian, daughter of Lily.

248
00:13:07,175 --> 00:13:10,480
You hurt their feelings on a night
they were feeling very fragile, so...

249
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:13,360
you can just shut up about my family,
Blanche Ramora Trickle,

250
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,890
or you'll end up...

251
00:13:15,415 --> 00:13:18,395
Well, I can't think
of anything worse than here, so...

252
00:13:18,855 --> 00:13:21,389
Snap! Now, touch her.
Touch her before she talks back.

253
00:13:21,429 --> 00:13:22,950
Touch her! Touch her! Touch her!

254
00:13:24,405 --> 00:13:25,805
That felt so good.

255
00:13:32,615 --> 00:13:34,520
That hapless shark was just a patsy?

256
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:36,579
He got a whiff of lard
in Blanche's hair gel

257
00:13:36,619 --> 00:13:38,000
and followed his instincts.

258
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:40,411
The killer would have needed access
to the <i>Dolls</i>' dressing room

259
00:13:40,451 --> 00:13:43,320
and the remote for the shark gate,
all of which hollers inside job.

260
00:13:43,555 --> 00:13:46,308
Suddenly, our <i>Aquacade</i> looks nastier
than a backed-up sink on Thanksgiving.

261
00:13:46,348 --> 00:13:49,043
There's no way our bad fish
is gonna nibble with a bunch of PIs

262
00:13:49,083 --> 00:13:51,065
coming trawling for murderers.

263
00:13:51,105 --> 00:13:52,560
What we need now is a cover.

264
00:13:53,925 --> 00:13:56,400
- My aunts!
- Lily. Vivian. A booth? Pie?

265
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,435
Pie and booth?

266
00:13:57,475 --> 00:14:00,280
Perhaps a sugar-free
apricot custard to go.

267
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,440
You are all really
co-ordinated today.

268
00:14:04,066 --> 00:14:08,000
Olive, we'd like back
the <i>Darling Mermaid Darling</i> costumes

269
00:14:08,081 --> 00:14:09,920
we gave you some time ago.

270
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:11,745
- Feeling nostalgic?
- No.

271
00:14:11,785 --> 00:14:15,720
We're joining the floating cast of Jimmy
Neptune's Night of a Thousand Bubbles.

272
00:14:15,905 --> 00:14:18,560
This is our living in sync
practice hour.

273
00:14:18,685 --> 00:14:19,975
OMG!

274
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:21,755
GR8!

275
00:14:22,005 --> 00:14:23,705
TTFN. No. BRB.

276
00:14:24,635 --> 00:14:26,800
She got a case of the dumbA-S-S.

277
00:14:27,425 --> 00:14:30,776
How about you take a seat
far over there where you can...

278
00:14:31,075 --> 00:14:32,480
do whatever it is you're doing?

279
00:14:37,615 --> 00:14:40,215
Well, ladies,
if it isn't a small sea.

280
00:14:40,915 --> 00:14:44,435
It just so happens I have business
at Jimmy Neptune's myself.

281
00:14:44,475 --> 00:14:47,175
Would you mind stepping
outside for a little chat?

282
00:14:47,215 --> 00:14:48,211
After you.

283
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,680
No stares of disbelief, I beg you.

284
00:15:00,155 --> 00:15:02,320
I couldn't pass up an all-access-pass
for the <i>Aquacade</i>.

285
00:15:02,525 --> 00:15:05,360
It may be all access, unfortunately,
it's not all inclusive.

286
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,720
I know, I can't go. But I don't care
cause they're back in the water for pay.

287
00:15:08,925 --> 00:15:10,953
But I want you there taking photos

288
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,360
and making notes
and then reporting back to me.

289
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,691
It doesn't seem fair,
like we're on Spring Break

290
00:15:15,731 --> 00:15:18,773
- while you're stuck in detention.
- This detention's easier 'cause...

291
00:15:18,813 --> 00:15:20,601
they're surrounded
by people who love them

292
00:15:20,641 --> 00:15:22,718
in this very emotional
and vulnerable time.

293
00:15:22,758 --> 00:15:25,047
You just make sure
that Emerson is a vigilant bodyguard

294
00:15:25,087 --> 00:15:26,760
and sticks to them like glue.

295
00:15:26,995 --> 00:15:27,845
Paddle out.

296
00:15:55,135 --> 00:15:57,385
Dipping a toe back
in our old lives...

297
00:15:57,735 --> 00:16:00,640
and solving a murder.
The thought brings tingles.

298
00:16:01,185 --> 00:16:03,085
All right, everybody.
Here's your assignments.

299
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:05,000
Itty-Bitty, you're hair and make-up.

300
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,928
I want you
to get into Blanche's dressing room

301
00:16:06,968 --> 00:16:08,415
and find that hair gel.

302
00:16:08,455 --> 00:16:11,480
Pie maker, you're the deal maker,
aka the <i>Mermaids</i>' agent.

303
00:16:11,725 --> 00:16:13,375
Stick to Jimmy Neptune.

304
00:16:13,625 --> 00:16:16,401
As team coach, I'll sidle up
to the <i>Aqua Dolls</i>' manager

305
00:16:16,441 --> 00:16:19,080
and grieving husband, Shane Trickle.

306
00:16:19,555 --> 00:16:22,916
And as team heavy, I'll also make sure
you two have nothing to worry about

307
00:16:22,956 --> 00:16:25,706
except scissor kicking ass
and taking names.

308
00:16:26,005 --> 00:16:28,600
Aqua Troops, circle round
for an important announcement.

309
00:16:28,775 --> 00:16:31,240
As terrible
as these circumstances are,

310
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:34,070
they've also brought us
something wonderful.

311
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,160
A pair of luminaries.

312
00:16:36,855 --> 00:16:38,410
Everyone, put your fins together

313
00:16:38,450 --> 00:16:41,600
for A Night of a Thousand Bubbles'
new headliners...

314
00:16:42,465 --> 00:16:44,320
The <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i>.

315
00:16:50,715 --> 00:16:52,315
That's bogus, Neptune!

316
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:54,560
We have a signed thing.

317
00:16:54,640 --> 00:16:57,480
Which I will honor by finding
a new act for Coral.

318
00:16:57,695 --> 00:17:00,000
Does anybody even know
who these two are?

319
00:17:00,455 --> 00:17:02,755
I met my husband
at a <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i> show.

320
00:17:02,795 --> 00:17:04,865
They're the reason
we devote our lives to this.

321
00:17:04,905 --> 00:17:06,279
I have pens for autographs.

322
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,680
I ought to punch you
in the snot locker!

323
00:17:10,225 --> 00:17:12,775
<i>As Lily and Vivian's stars
began to rise,</i>

324
00:17:13,095 --> 00:17:16,495
<i>Olive encountered another star
that was about to fall.</i>

325
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:25,680
- Are you the new sea horse?
- Heavens to hamstrings.

326
00:17:25,905 --> 00:17:29,800
No. I'm Sally Boots. Fly girl
to the <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i>.

327
00:17:30,075 --> 00:17:32,634
Snap that G-string! I love them.

328
00:17:32,859 --> 00:17:33,924
I love you.

329
00:17:37,095 --> 00:17:38,345
Mama.

330
00:17:40,565 --> 00:17:42,040
- Who are you?
- Sid Tango.

331
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,920
- I open the second act.
- Why aren't you out there?

332
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,600
They're relocating me.

333
00:17:46,955 --> 00:17:49,455
- Out by the porta-lights.
- Shoot.

334
00:17:49,665 --> 00:17:52,228
There's enough room
in this fishbowl for all us fish.

335
00:17:52,268 --> 00:17:53,640
You know what? Thank you.

336
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,240
If only more people around here
would be as accepting of who I am.

337
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:58,040
People aren't accepting here?

338
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:00,989
Being a man in aqua entertainment...

339
00:18:01,315 --> 00:18:03,120
Which is to say
unappreciated and invisible.

340
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:06,015
Do you know how many times Jimmy
promised me the headliner spot?

341
00:18:06,055 --> 00:18:07,755
Thought I'd get it
after Blanche kicked.

342
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,600
Then I hear they're dragging
the musty mermaids out of retirement.

343
00:18:10,905 --> 00:18:13,200
Oh, hell.
Some day it'll be my turn.

344
00:18:13,495 --> 00:18:15,800
Until then, I'll be content
watching others...

345
00:18:16,445 --> 00:18:18,000
glimmer and gleam.

346
00:18:18,227 --> 00:18:22,011
<i>Ironically, Olive found those same words
staring back at her</i>

347
00:18:22,051 --> 00:18:24,801
<i>from the vicinity
of Coral's dressing table.</i>

348
00:18:28,395 --> 00:18:29,773
She'd mind if I borrow this?

349
00:18:29,813 --> 00:18:33,040
My girls need a touch-up before
splash-down. Nice to meet you. Bye.

350
00:18:34,525 --> 00:18:36,353
I combed the dressing room
for the weapon.

351
00:18:36,393 --> 00:18:38,293
Well, murder weapon trigger.

352
00:18:38,345 --> 00:18:42,095
Blanche's beauty area had been broomed,
but I did found Coral's hair gel.

353
00:18:42,155 --> 00:18:43,405
It smells fine.

354
00:18:44,545 --> 00:18:45,995
Nice work, Sea-Wee.

355
00:18:46,545 --> 00:18:48,955
I got a great big bucket
full of nothing.

356
00:18:48,995 --> 00:18:50,895
Still, your find
does prove our theory.

357
00:18:50,935 --> 00:18:52,535
Blanche was definitely the target.

358
00:18:58,055 --> 00:19:02,022
Holy Ibiza, Monaco and St Tropez.
That is some banana hammock.

359
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:05,175
That's Sid Tango. I found him hanging
in Blanche's dressing room.

360
00:19:05,215 --> 00:19:07,352
He's sort of fun
and just a teensy bit angry

361
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,925
he was overlooked to lead
the <i>Aquacade</i> due to his...

362
00:19:09,965 --> 00:19:11,192
Well, because of...

363
00:19:11,725 --> 00:19:15,240
- what's in his banana hammock.
- I really should look away, but I...

364
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,000
- I can't.
- Wanna go blind?

365
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:19,930
I wanna catch a killer.
Look at the shark pen.

366
00:19:21,275 --> 00:19:22,225
See that?

367
00:19:22,575 --> 00:19:24,960
It happens every time
Sid touches his belt.

368
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:32,400
Come on.

369
00:19:35,378 --> 00:19:36,800
Excuse me. This is where I dive.

370
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:39,440
Well, you're about
to belly flop, all right...

371
00:19:41,725 --> 00:19:44,760
... right into a little cesspool
I like to call the county pen.

372
00:19:54,355 --> 00:19:55,960
- What do you want, Tango?
- You.

373
00:19:56,825 --> 00:19:58,960
- To get me out of here.
- Life on the inside rough?

374
00:19:59,735 --> 00:20:03,210
I'll call in a favor to the warden.
Maybe he can ease up a little.

375
00:20:03,395 --> 00:20:04,945
What? He's a regular.

376
00:20:05,045 --> 00:20:07,834
Sometimes I serve his pecan pie
with an extra scoop of caramel sauce,

377
00:20:07,874 --> 00:20:08,946
complimentary like.

378
00:20:08,986 --> 00:20:11,840
This was a frame job! I had
nothing to do with killing Blanche.

379
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:14,480
Why would I keep
the murder weapon in my Speedo?

380
00:20:14,605 --> 00:20:17,705
Why don't you say that
and do a dance for the judge, Tango?

381
00:20:17,745 --> 00:20:20,181
You had opportunity
and you had motive.

382
00:20:20,221 --> 00:20:23,080
You told me that you were jealous
of the <i>Aqua Dolls</i>' headliner spot.

383
00:20:23,215 --> 00:20:25,240
My jealousy has nothing
to do with them.

384
00:20:25,435 --> 00:20:27,840
It stems from loving an art form
that doesn't love me back.

385
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:30,045
Why aren't you shining
your spotlight on Coral?

386
00:20:30,085 --> 00:20:32,240
- It's what she's wanted all her life.
- Keep splashing.

387
00:20:32,364 --> 00:20:35,765
There may have been two <i>Aqua Dolls</i>,
but it was really The Blanche Show.

388
00:20:35,805 --> 00:20:38,655
She always put herself first.
Coral hated her for it.

389
00:20:38,766 --> 00:20:42,520
Are you thinking she got tired of living
in big sissy's shadow and engineered it?

390
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,960
Coral launched Blanche
into the direction of that shark.

391
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,739
It's certainly a thing
to make you go...

392
00:20:47,961 --> 00:20:50,430
<i>As Emerson Cod
let Sid Tango off the hook,</i>

393
00:20:50,626 --> 00:20:54,280
<i>the private detective's suspicions
side-stroked back to the </i>Aquacade.

394
00:20:56,149 --> 00:20:57,504
What's the matter with you?

395
00:20:57,544 --> 00:20:59,004
I am warning you, ass.

396
00:20:59,777 --> 00:21:02,520
Why don't you just take that trident
and stab me in the heart?

397
00:21:02,601 --> 00:21:04,360
Pack your spandex. You're fired!

398
00:21:05,563 --> 00:21:07,320
Everybody, chillax.
I can fix this.

399
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:11,104
Save it, centrabrains.//
You're as useless as teats on a boar.

400
00:21:12,201 --> 00:21:13,178
Teats.

401
00:21:13,865 --> 00:21:15,155
Coral, wait!

402
00:21:17,487 --> 00:21:19,674
Can you believe the claws
on that sea monster?

403
00:21:19,714 --> 00:21:22,720
Trying to pinch my <i>Aquacade</i>
and turn it into a vehicle for herself!

404
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:25,377
- Talent. They're like children.
- Do you know what she tried to pitch?

405
00:21:25,417 --> 00:21:27,560
A one-woman tribute
to a chorus line!

406
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:30,338
- Don't you need a chorus and a line?
- She figured out a way around it!

407
00:21:30,378 --> 00:21:32,640
The last thing I need
is another water dancer.

408
00:21:33,172 --> 00:21:36,971
With Galveston Gus gone, the audience
is thirsting for a daredevil act.

409
00:21:37,918 --> 00:21:38,855
Picture this.

410
00:21:38,895 --> 00:21:40,939
A motorcycle, but it's on fire.

411
00:21:41,251 --> 00:21:43,977
And there's a ramp,
20 feet high, on fire too.

412
00:21:44,082 --> 00:21:45,640
- A rider appears...
- Also on fire?

413
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:48,008
Better. In chains.
She guns the engine,

414
00:21:48,048 --> 00:21:50,109
soars off the ramp, through a hoop,

415
00:21:50,149 --> 00:21:52,369
maybe flaming, maybe not.
I'll have to crunch the numbers.

416
00:21:52,409 --> 00:21:54,560
- and then lands on the other side.
- She?

417
00:21:54,641 --> 00:21:57,808
Yes, Coral or at least it was supposed
to be her until I canned her.

418
00:21:58,091 --> 00:22:00,960
Still, don't you think that's an act
that will put butts in seats?

419
00:22:01,041 --> 00:22:04,240
Absolutely and I've got another act
that butts absolutely love.

420
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:05,833
Of course, The <i>Darlings</i>' contract.

421
00:22:05,873 --> 00:22:07,863
Some sticking points,
but no tsunami-sized.

422
00:22:07,903 --> 00:22:08,998
- Whatever.
- Yes?

423
00:22:09,082 --> 00:22:12,040
I came up with stuff they don't need,
to see if we could get away with it.

424
00:22:12,121 --> 00:22:14,134
Charles sisters
are as easy as a lazy river.

425
00:22:14,174 --> 00:22:17,040
It'd be my pleasure to have them aboard,
on one condition.

426
00:22:19,743 --> 00:22:22,040
Great news.
Jimmy agreed to all of your demands.

427
00:22:22,121 --> 00:22:24,226
The fresh lilacs?
The Egyptian cotton towels?

428
00:22:24,266 --> 00:22:26,800
- The vodka fountain?
- The papers will be ready tomorrow.

429
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:29,422
But just so you know,
it all hinges on one thing.

430
00:22:29,462 --> 00:22:31,860
Jimmy's gonna take the <i>Aquacade</i>
on a European tour,

431
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,120
signing means you'll go.

432
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:35,600
No way!
Who would take care of the birds?

433
00:22:35,681 --> 00:22:38,347
Place flowers on Charlotte's grave?
And besides...

434
00:22:39,638 --> 00:22:41,355
Lily has indulged me enough.

435
00:22:41,730 --> 00:22:43,655
- So our answer is...
- Yes.

436
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,777
For the first time
since Charlotte died,

437
00:22:48,849 --> 00:22:51,008
maybe it's OK
to leave sadness behind.

438
00:22:51,768 --> 00:22:53,714
Start putting our happiness first.

439
00:22:54,838 --> 00:22:55,920
What do you think?

440
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:58,481
I think Chuck... Charlotte,

441
00:22:58,658 --> 00:23:02,139
as you described her,
was a wonderful caring woman and she,

442
00:23:02,179 --> 00:23:04,560
like me, would want you
to put your happiness first too.

443
00:23:05,135 --> 00:23:08,240
I think we're all in agreement
when I say: "Swim on, <i>Mermaids</i>".

444
00:23:10,286 --> 00:23:11,720
Oh, my... It's Coral!

445
00:23:15,030 --> 00:23:16,467
Everybody stand back.

446
00:23:16,727 --> 00:23:17,800
I was a lifeguard.

447
00:23:18,194 --> 00:23:20,200
- Was she attacked?
- We saw the whole thing.

448
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:22,640
She chained herself up,
hopped on the chopper and rode it

449
00:23:22,721 --> 00:23:24,840
like a Hell's Angel in drag
until she fell in.

450
00:23:25,155 --> 00:23:27,059
It would have been funny
if it wasn't so tragic.

451
00:23:29,320 --> 00:23:31,242
What the hell were you doing?

452
00:23:31,282 --> 00:23:33,600
Jimmy. Is that you, Jimmy?

453
00:23:33,681 --> 00:23:34,960
Yes!

454
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:37,079
I was just trying to show you
that I could do it.

455
00:23:37,119 --> 00:23:38,920
That daredevil act that you wanted.

456
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:41,840
I will do anything if it means
getting back into the show.

457
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,989
Is that so wrong?

458
00:23:43,029 --> 00:23:45,308
