- A bunch of them, really.

524
00:26:20,621 --> 00:26:22,840
Downing Street, the autobahn,

525
00:26:23,421 --> 00:26:24,743
the Champs Elysees.

526
00:26:26,024 --> 00:26:28,240
They're European, as in Europe.

527
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:29,320
That's right.

528
00:26:31,811 --> 00:26:33,211
Didn't expect fake surprise,

529
00:26:33,251 --> 00:26:35,714
but I didn't expect
stunned silence either.

530
00:26:39,654 --> 00:26:42,140
- How could you let this happen?
- I did what you told me.

531
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:45,281
- I thought you'd be happy.
- Ned, they think I'm dead!

532
00:26:45,968 --> 00:26:49,088
This has been bearable
because I've been keeping tabs on them.

533
00:26:49,128 --> 00:26:52,363
If they needed something,
I could help them or try and fix it.

534
00:26:52,403 --> 00:26:55,047
While I'm completely removed,
I'm still part of their lives.

535
00:26:55,087 --> 00:26:57,690
And how can I be part of their lives
if they're in Europe?

536
00:27:00,482 --> 00:27:02,595
- This is a game changer.
- What game?

537
00:27:02,635 --> 00:27:05,173
- This is not a game.
- No, it's not a game. It's my life.

538
00:27:05,933 --> 00:27:08,040
And now you decided
to modify the rules,

539
00:27:08,331 --> 00:27:10,760
I've gotta re-evaluate
which ones actually keep me here.

540
00:27:17,423 --> 00:27:19,880
I'll just sit here and try
to concentrate on not throwing up.

541
00:27:21,263 --> 00:27:22,856
Butterflies making you queasy?

542
00:27:22,896 --> 00:27:25,104
What say we drown them
with a dip in the vodka fountain?

543
00:27:25,479 --> 00:27:27,008
I never drink and dive.

544
00:27:27,550 --> 00:27:29,320
It's disrespectful to the audience,

545
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,962
more importantly, to Vivian.

546
00:27:32,055 --> 00:27:32,992
Where is she?

547
00:27:33,148 --> 00:27:34,990
Meeting with the sound tech.

548
00:27:35,221 --> 00:27:37,400
The underwater speaker
sounded muddy in rehearsal.

549
00:27:38,611 --> 00:27:41,000
Well, let's hope
they solve it by show time.

550
00:27:41,081 --> 00:27:44,173
<i>Coral had slept
with her own sister's husband.</i>

551
00:27:44,213 --> 00:27:47,000
<i>Lily had done the same
with her sister's fiancé.</i>

552
00:27:47,397 --> 00:27:49,439
<i>The symmetry made her feel
as if she were looking</i>

553
00:27:49,521 --> 00:27:51,175
<i>at a reflection of herself.</i>

554
00:27:51,518 --> 00:27:54,804
<i>And since herself
was what she hated most, </i>

555
00:27:54,844 --> 00:27:56,480
<i>she rejected the mirror.</i>

556
00:27:56,785 --> 00:27:59,880
Say, what is our choreography
at measure 120 again?

557
00:28:00,049 --> 00:28:02,840
Are we reverse craning
into a ballet leg thrust?

558
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:05,919
- Full corkscrew first.
- I thought the corkscrew came last.

559
00:28:07,210 --> 00:28:10,395
Hold it. That's right,
which makes you wrong.

560
00:28:10,435 --> 00:28:13,107
The corkscrew comes last.
You're losing it, Lil.

561
00:28:13,147 --> 00:28:14,794
I think I'll have
that nip after all.

562
00:28:14,834 --> 00:28:16,440
- Sure?
- Hey, short round.

563
00:28:16,520 --> 00:28:18,303
A little help with my bun.

564
00:28:22,981 --> 00:28:25,000
- You've got something poking out.
- Leave it!

565
00:28:25,950 --> 00:28:27,680
Sorry, but when I see a string,
I just...

566
00:28:31,348 --> 00:28:32,677
- I have to yank it!
- Hey!

567
00:28:33,583 --> 00:28:35,080
Holy gold lamé!

568
00:28:36,799 --> 00:28:38,880
You're trying
to be a singular sensation!

569
00:28:39,327 --> 00:28:42,586
You swam your way back to the <i>Aquacade</i>
by preying on Vivian's sympathy.

570
00:28:42,626 --> 00:28:45,186
You tried to break up the <i>Darlings</i>
by stage frightening Lily

571
00:28:45,226 --> 00:28:49,033
so you can rule the pool in a one-woman
chorus line. Where's the top hat?

572
00:28:49,073 --> 00:28:50,960
- I'm gonna shove it up your...
- Olive,

573
00:28:51,644 --> 00:28:52,560
excuse us.

574
00:28:57,920 --> 00:29:01,103
Did you know my sister
was born with a hole in her heart?

575
00:29:02,290 --> 00:29:04,308
The doctors fixed it, but...

576
00:29:04,849 --> 00:29:08,346
sometimes it leaks a bit
and stuff gets through...

577
00:29:09,584 --> 00:29:10,725
stuff like you.

578
00:29:11,183 --> 00:29:13,930
Vivian may think that a woman
who sleeps with her sister's husband

579
00:29:13,970 --> 00:29:15,880
deserves a second chance,
but I don't.

580
00:29:16,126 --> 00:29:18,551
You'll always be what you are...

581
00:29:19,029 --> 00:29:21,640
a selfish, conniving wretch.

582
00:29:21,890 --> 00:29:23,520
The <i>Darling Mermaid Darlings</i>

583
00:29:23,909 --> 00:29:26,063
are a team that puts
each other first,

584
00:29:26,833 --> 00:29:29,008
so get in your show boat...

585
00:29:29,206 --> 00:29:30,799
and row it to hell.

586
00:29:32,099 --> 00:29:34,732
This putting others first
that you're so proud of,

587
00:29:34,772 --> 00:29:37,522
I assume it didn't apply
to your baby.

588
00:29:39,281 --> 00:29:41,409
- I never had a baby.
- That's what Vivian said.

589
00:29:41,449 --> 00:29:45,091
We were just making small talk
and I casually asked her

590
00:29:45,131 --> 00:29:46,984
if you had a son
or a daughter and she...

591
00:29:47,181 --> 00:29:49,280
told me
that neither of you had any children.

592
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,740
Isn't that strange?

593
00:29:51,230 --> 00:29:52,739
The world's full of spinsters.

594
00:29:52,779 --> 00:29:54,800
You know, 30 years ago, you and I

595
00:29:55,404 --> 00:29:57,860
changed next to each other
after a show

596
00:29:58,089 --> 00:30:00,904
and the seamstress
had to let out your costume,

597
00:30:01,435 --> 00:30:03,942
the flippers didn't fit your feet
and you had that just...

598
00:30:03,982 --> 00:30:06,002
knocked up glow about you.

599
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:08,591
And then you disappeared
for nine months.

600
00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:13,431
So where's the kid, spinster?

601
00:30:13,962 --> 00:30:15,814
And why are you hiding it
from Vivian?

602
00:30:15,854 --> 00:30:17,963
Breathe another word
and it'll be your last!

603
00:30:18,003 --> 00:30:20,320
- Now get out!
- You'll regret this.

604
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,445
- Coral had to cancel. She's sick.
- Then it's just us...

605
00:30:31,756 --> 00:30:33,786
as it really should be, I suppose.

606
00:30:33,994 --> 00:30:34,800
Ready?

607
00:30:35,312 --> 00:30:36,120
I can't.

608
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:39,800
We've come this far.

609
00:30:40,994 --> 00:30:43,357
This time, don't do it for me,

610
00:30:44,845 --> 00:30:45,800
do it for you.

611
00:30:51,164 --> 00:30:54,960
<i>Meanwhile, the </i>Darling Mermaid Darlings<i>'
one-man security detail</i>

612
00:30:55,041 --> 00:30:57,209
<i>spied a lurking shadow.</i>

613
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:02,699
Hell, yeah.

614
00:31:02,739 --> 00:31:05,520
<i>Which called to mind a murderous surfer
named Shane.</i>

615
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:07,601
Trickle, down on the ground!

616
00:31:07,641 --> 00:31:10,680
Dead girl, don't you know
there's a killer on the loose?

617
00:31:11,851 --> 00:31:14,360
Think again, fool!
Now, step out with your hands up!

618
00:31:24,058 --> 00:31:26,160
- What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

619
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,669
- I asked you first.
- The person who's sneaking around

620
00:31:28,709 --> 00:31:30,220
in the dark wearing a damn disguise

621
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:32,677
is usually the person
with the most explaining to do.

622
00:31:35,248 --> 00:31:36,920
That'd be you, dead girl.

623
00:31:37,111 --> 00:31:38,402
Well, I came up here...

624
00:31:38,442 --> 00:31:40,880
to get a better vantage point
of Lily and Vivian swimming.

625
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:43,364
That's a lie. From my excellent vantage
point in the shadows,

626
00:31:43,404 --> 00:31:45,520
I saw her take their music
out of the CD player.

627
00:31:45,601 --> 00:31:47,822
I did not. Look, it's still in here.
Look. See?

628
00:31:47,862 --> 00:31:50,960
Cause I put it back in there.
I feel really ashamed now. I'm so sorry.

629
00:31:51,041 --> 00:31:52,866
You're also really lousy
at explaining things

630
00:31:52,906 --> 00:31:55,011
cause the more you talk,
the more lost I get.

631
00:31:55,051 --> 00:31:57,161
I was really happy
for Lily and Vivian until...

632
00:31:57,286 --> 00:31:58,959
their happiness
threatened my happiness.

633
00:31:59,043 --> 00:32:01,856
So in a moment of weakness and panic,
I snook up here and I...

634
00:32:02,428 --> 00:32:04,736
tried to sabotage their show
in the hope that they'd stay.

635
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:06,187
Despicable.

636
00:32:07,297 --> 00:32:08,413
Now you.

637
00:32:09,326 --> 00:32:12,126
I guess I must have thought
Chuck would try to do something rash,

638
00:32:12,501 --> 00:32:14,260
so I came up here to stop her.

639
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:17,280
Here's the <i>Pie Hole</i> mellow mix
you asked me to get out of my car.

640
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:20,434
You know what I realized
on my full tilt run back up here?

641
00:32:21,110 --> 00:32:23,159
First, there's a lot of steps
in this place.

642
00:32:23,199 --> 00:32:25,560
The second, Lily never mentioned
a last minute music change.

643
00:32:26,042 --> 00:32:27,218
There wasn't.

644
00:32:27,258 --> 00:32:29,996
Pie boy here was gonna torpedo
their performance.

645
00:32:30,621 --> 00:32:32,479
How could you?

646
00:32:36,095 --> 00:32:38,634
When Chuck's happiness was threatened
by Lily and Vivian's happiness,

647
00:32:38,674 --> 00:32:41,960
my happiness freaked out, I thought
Chuck would follow them to Europe.

648
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:45,310
I'm a solo guy by nature,

649
00:32:46,018 --> 00:32:48,849
but I choose to affiliate myself
with the both of you.

650
00:32:49,296 --> 00:32:50,463
The reason being...

651
00:32:50,848 --> 00:32:53,502
'cause when you spend all your time
chasing bad guys,

652
00:32:53,542 --> 00:32:55,594
you want the best of the good guys
in your corner.

653
00:32:57,126 --> 00:32:59,863
You two normally
are as solid as they come

654
00:32:59,903 --> 00:33:03,100
because your moral compass
is always pointed due...

655
00:33:04,276 --> 00:33:05,640
the right thing.

656
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,600
But clearly,

657
00:33:08,742 --> 00:33:11,040
someone's been screwing
with both your magnetic fields

658
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:13,118
'cause the both of you seem
really lost right now.

659
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:15,957
So I'm gonna help you out
by personally escorting and...

660
00:33:15,997 --> 00:33:19,673
them physically ejecting both
of your asses from these premises.

661
00:33:19,713 --> 00:33:21,421
Now, what do you think about that?

662
00:33:25,491 --> 00:33:29,780
<i>At that moment, Charlotte Charles
walk of shame turned into triumph.</i>

663
00:33:56,559 --> 00:34:00,036
<i>The beat of their happy hearts
and the blare of the underwater speakers</i>

664
00:34:00,076 --> 00:34:02,762
<i>drowned out the sound
of impending doom.</i>

665
00:34:12,628 --> 00:34:13,880
I did it for you, Coral!

666
00:34:14,106 --> 00:34:15,840
Nobody asked you to, Shane.

667
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:18,520
You know what's great about
everyone's thinking that you're stupid?

668
00:34:18,747 --> 00:34:21,720
They assume that you can't get away
with murder, but I did!

669
00:34:21,942 --> 00:34:24,902
You also sent a shark
into the water while I was swimming.

670
00:34:24,942 --> 00:34:26,641
Did you think about that, Professor?

671
00:34:26,681 --> 00:34:28,920
Yes! It's why I smeared your costume

672
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:31,639
