of the Red Sea Moses sole.

673
00:34:31,720 --> 00:34:33,560
A little-known shark repellent.

674
00:34:34,192 --> 00:34:36,400
Why don't you just drop
the microphone there, Trickle?

675
00:34:36,871 --> 00:34:39,119
I plan to... in the pool!

676
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:41,437
Because the cord will shoot out
a current through the water

677
00:34:41,477 --> 00:34:43,399
and electrocute the <i>Darlings</i>.

678
00:34:43,495 --> 00:34:46,840
Once Lily and Vivian Charles are dead,
Jimmy will finally have

679
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:49,720
to make you the star of the show.
And that's all you ever wanted.

680
00:34:51,193 --> 00:34:53,257
- Now I get it.
- Look at me, Coral!

681
00:34:53,297 --> 00:34:55,320
It's all for you!

682
00:34:56,769 --> 00:34:58,269
Dang!

683
00:35:22,350 --> 00:35:26,606
<i>With the victory of the previous night
faded in the light of a conversation</i>

684
00:35:26,646 --> 00:35:28,440
<i>- that had to be had.</i>
- Morning.

685
00:35:29,801 --> 00:35:32,760
I hope that gift's not for me.
My half birthday is over.

686
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:36,560
The gifts I gave you before
only triggered crisis and misery.

687
00:35:36,879 --> 00:35:38,542
Really? I hadn't noticed.

688
00:35:39,440 --> 00:35:40,720
Give this one a shot?

689
00:35:48,090 --> 00:35:50,822
I don't remember this picture.
I remember the day, but

690
00:35:50,862 --> 00:35:51,800
not the shot.

691
00:35:51,881 --> 00:35:53,800
Because I took it
with my junior instamatic.

692
00:35:53,881 --> 00:35:55,702
It was the first time
I met your aunts.

693
00:35:56,097 --> 00:35:57,455
They were buzzing through town

694
00:35:57,495 --> 00:35:59,627
on their way
to some far-off and fantastic place.

695
00:35:59,667 --> 00:36:01,904
I had almost forgotten
those aunts, so...

696
00:36:02,820 --> 00:36:04,120
thank you for reminding me.

697
00:36:04,610 --> 00:36:07,490
Chuck, I tried very hard
to be a good boyfriend.

698
00:36:08,479 --> 00:36:10,854
I believe that every day,
even in the smallest ways,

699
00:36:10,894 --> 00:36:12,920
I try to put your happiness
before my own.

700
00:36:13,289 --> 00:36:15,040
Yeah, I agree
with that whole-heartedly.

701
00:36:16,963 --> 00:36:18,240
I've been lying to you,

702
00:36:19,107 --> 00:36:20,680
not that it's any kind of excuse,

703
00:36:20,761 --> 00:36:23,074
but I think it's because
I've been lying to myself too.

704
00:36:23,114 --> 00:36:25,378
If Lily and Vivian knew
you were still alive

705
00:36:25,418 --> 00:36:27,040
the only person
in danger would be me.

706
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:30,943
The danger itself is a lie.

707
00:36:30,983 --> 00:36:32,952
It's irrational fear
in danger's clothing.

708
00:36:32,992 --> 00:36:35,252
It's whispering,
"Chuck loves her mother and aunt

709
00:36:35,292 --> 00:36:38,061
so much she wouldn't want to spend
her life with you if she...

710
00:36:38,385 --> 00:36:39,839
could be with them."

711
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:42,313
And so I put my happiness
first and...

712
00:36:43,603 --> 00:36:46,141
told everyone that no-one could know
that you're alive again,

713
00:36:46,838 --> 00:36:48,920
especially Lily and Vivian Charles.

714
00:36:49,148 --> 00:36:51,315
- You didn't know what you were doing.
- I do now.

715
00:36:52,595 --> 00:36:53,731
And now...

716
00:36:55,790 --> 00:36:58,325
I'm finally putting
your happiness before my own.

717
00:37:08,496 --> 00:37:11,727
<i>At this very moment,
a life event was taking place.</i>

718
00:37:12,581 --> 00:37:16,983
<i>Lily Charles had begun to experience
feelings that had become foreign.</i>

719
00:37:17,023 --> 00:37:19,535
<i>These pleasant sensations...</i>

720
00:37:19,722 --> 00:37:20,760
<i>were not to last.</i>

721
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,389
Coral and I...

722
00:37:27,847 --> 00:37:30,543
just had an illuminating
conversation,

723
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:34,360
one that helped me put together
the pieces of a 30-year-old mystery.

724
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:38,838
There was a part of me
that always knew,

725
00:37:39,390 --> 00:37:42,479
but I wouldn't allow myself
to entertain such horrid thoughts

726
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:44,480
that my beloved sister

727
00:37:44,726 --> 00:37:46,040
would go behind my back

728
00:37:46,422 --> 00:37:48,200
with my fiancé

729
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,680
and have a child.

730
00:37:51,413 --> 00:37:53,080
It was Charlotte, wasn't it?

731
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:57,960
I tried thousands
of times to tell you,

732
00:37:58,403 --> 00:37:59,920
but I couldn't find a way to do it.

733
00:38:00,145 --> 00:38:02,056
Why do you think
I hid from the world?

734
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:05,521
I was so ashamed I couldn't bear
to have anyone look at me.

735
00:38:05,719 --> 00:38:08,360
I understand.
I can't bear to look at you either.

736
00:38:11,299 --> 00:38:13,920
I took the liberty
of calling you a cab.

737
00:38:14,493 --> 00:38:15,840
Where am I supposed to go?

738
00:38:16,356 --> 00:38:18,115
Anywhere but here.

739
00:38:20,634 --> 00:38:24,005
You know, I have spent half a lifetime
trying to make amends.

740
00:38:25,836 --> 00:38:28,614
I gave up the only man
I have ever loved,

741
00:38:29,602 --> 00:38:31,611
as well as my beautiful
baby daughter,

742
00:38:32,673 --> 00:38:34,914
because I knew the truth
would break your heart.

743
00:38:36,475 --> 00:38:38,150
So I broke mine instead.

744
00:38:39,427 --> 00:38:42,120
I did what I have done
since the day you were born...

745
00:38:43,676 --> 00:38:45,520
chose your happiness over mine.

746
00:38:46,369 --> 00:38:47,800
You don't have to anymore.

747
00:38:50,646 --> 00:38:51,640
All right!

748
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:03,657
<i>At that very moment, time stopped,
as it is one to do</i>

749
00:39:03,697 --> 00:39:06,243
<i>when present,
past and future collide.</i>

750
00:39:06,764 --> 00:39:08,564
<i>When one's existence ceases</i>

751
00:39:08,604 --> 00:39:10,640
<i>to be measured in days,
hours and minutes,</i>

752
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:14,681
<i>but instead in the immeasurable
quantity of life events.</i>

753
00:39:15,253 --> 00:39:19,115
<i>For Lily and Vivian Charles,
the reappearance of a daughter and niece</i>

754
00:39:19,155 --> 00:39:22,000
<i>was a life event
that would eventually overshadow</i>

755
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:24,021
<i>a 30-year-old betrayal</i>

756
00:39:24,061 --> 00:39:26,457
<i>and result in a splash of water,</i>

757
00:39:26,497 --> 00:39:29,328
<i>the roar of the crowd
and a whirlwind tour</i>

758
00:39:29,368 --> 00:39:31,555
<i>around the world... twice.</i>

759
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:35,900
<i>Private investigator Emerson Cod
would experience a life event</i>

760
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:38,828
<i>when life found him
through the pages of a pop-up book </i>

761
00:39:38,868 --> 00:39:41,457
<i>and he was reunited
with his own Little Gum Shoe.</i>

762
00:39:41,497 --> 00:39:43,320
I'm looking for Emerson Cod.

763
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:53,720
<i>Jockey-cum-waitress-cum
private investigator Olive Snook</i>

764
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:56,657
<i>would experience
two life events in quick succession.</i>

765
00:39:56,880 --> 00:40:00,440
<i>The first, opening her heart
to a formerly friendless taxidermist</i>

766
00:40:00,521 --> 00:40:03,240
<i>and the second, by opening
a culinary palace dedicated</i>

767
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:06,968
<i> to the art of macaroni and cheese
called</i> The Intrepid Cow.

768
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:10,760
<i>For the pie maker
and the dead girl named Chuck,</i>

769
00:40:11,082 --> 00:40:13,440
<i>their shared life event
began with a touch</i>

770
00:40:13,611 --> 00:40:16,650
<i>and became the promise
of a new family, brought about</i>

771
00:40:16,690 --> 00:40:18,360
<i>- by the words...</i>
- I'm alive.

772
00:40:22,078 --> 00:40:24,853
<i>At that moment,
in the town of Coeur d'Coeurs,</i>

773
00:40:24,893 --> 00:40:27,444
<i>events occurred that are not,
were not</i>

774
00:40:27,484 --> 00:40:30,192
<i>and should never be
considered an ending.</i>

775
00:40:30,232 --> 00:40:33,112
<i>For endings, as it is known,
are where we begin.</i>

